  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To display SpriteKit content in a watch app, you use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/watchkit/wkinterfaceskscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", whereas on iOS, macOS, and tvOS, you use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to display a SpriteKit scene. If you need to mix SpriteKit with any custom Metal content, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skrenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ".  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SKRenderer is not available on watchOS."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "On iOS, tvOS, and macOS, Draw Using a View or a Renderer",
          "anchor": "3017237"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Choose from the options below to display SpriteKit content on iOS, tvOS, or macOS. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 4,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Draw Using a View",
          "anchor": "3017236"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To draw SpriteKit content the most common way, set up an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and set its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skview/1520084-scene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/drawing_spritekit_content_in_a_view"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for an example of using "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 4,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Draw Using a Renderer",
          "anchor": "2985160"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you want to mix SpriteKit content with your own Metal content, use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skrenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to draw your "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". You might use "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKRenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to replace specific portions of a SpriteKit app with custom Metal code, or vice versa. "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKRenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " combines the full control of Metal with the ease of use of SpriteKit and its library of useful objects. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For example, to take full control of just your game's tiled background while using SpriteKit to draw the rest, use an "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKRenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "MTLView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " combination instead of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and then write the tiled background code yourself in Metal."
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you're ready to mix the SpriteKit content with the Metal content, you call "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKRenderer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "'s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skrenderer/2866073-renderwithviewport"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Finally, call "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metal/mtlcommandbuffer/1443029-presentdrawable"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " on a Metal view when you're ready to present a frame.  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "On watchOS, Draw Using an Interface Scene",
          "anchor": "3017238"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To display SpriteKit content on Apple Watch, you create a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/watchkit/wkinterfaceskscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and then set its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/watchkit/wkinterfaceskscene/1650798-scene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/watchkit/wkinterfaceskscene"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " functions much like "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SKView"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", but without the debugging visualization options. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
